%p
  Use the following scale to determine the correct rating for the asset. You
  can enter fractional values such as <strong>4.5</strong> or <strong>2.75</strong> .

%dl.dl-horizontal
  - condition_types = ConditionType.all.reverse
  - condition_types.each_with_index do |type, index|
    - if type.name != "Unknown"
      %dt{:style => 'width:80px;margin-bottom:10px;'}= "#{sprintf("%#.2f", condition_types[index + 1].rating_ceiling + 0.01)} - #{sprintf("%#.2f", type.rating_ceiling)}"
      %dd{:style => 'margin-left:100px;;margin-bottom:5px;'}= "#{type.name} - #{type.description}"

%p
  Note that the FTA ranks any asset with a condition rating <strong>&lt 2.5</strong> as in need of replacement.

